Here are the contents for the file `public/index.html`:

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Community Center</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
    <link rel="icon" href="assets/favicon.ico" type="image/x-icon">
</head>
<body>
    <div id="root"></div>
    <script src="../src/index.js" type="module"></script>
</body>
</html>

And here are the contents for the file `public/styles.css`:

body {
    margin: 0;
    font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif;
    background-color: #f4f4f4;
    color: #333;
}

header {
    background: #007bff;
    color: #fff;
    padding: 10px 0;
    text-align: center;
}

footer {
    background: #333;
    color: #fff;
    text-align: center;
    padding: 10px 0;
    position: relative;
    bottom: 0;
    width: 100%;
}

h1, h2, h3 {
    margin: 0;
}

.container {
    width: 80%;
    margin: auto;
    overflow: hidden;
}

a {
    color: #007bff;
    text-decoration: none;
}

a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
}

And the folders for images and fonts should be created as specified:

public/assets/images/  # Folder for storing images
public/assets/fonts/   # Folder for custom fonts